    • isValid

      public boolean isValid(Object toTest)
      Is the supplied test object something that matches against our field definition regular expression?

      If validation optional is set to true this will return true, if the supplied object is null, this will always return false. Other-wise this will call toString and then match the field definition regex tp confirm the object matches our desired value.

      Specified by:
      isValid in interface uk.pallas.systems.typr.entities.v1.FieldDefinition
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      false if the object fails the validation match.
